            "created_at": "2018-05-07T17:25:31Z",
            "updated_at": "2018-05-07T17:25:31Z",
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> The plan is to log errors without debug flag set by default with Flask 1.0. It trips up too many users.\r\n\r\nSorry to zombie this, but did this make it into the recent versions? I'm experiencing that app.logger (aka logging.getLogger('flask.app')) **does not** log uncaught route/request exceptions when Flask.debug is False, but **does** log uncaught route/request exceptions when Flask.debug is True."
